Rating: 0
If you bake this in a diferent size pan, you will have to allow for different baking time. Also, if you use pyrex instead of metal, you will have to adjust the oven temperature as well. If you do bake it in a 9x13" pan, then cut into two to layer, you will have difficulty icing the cake...the crumbs on the cut side of the cake will come loose, and interfere with the icing. Probably not a good idea.

