Rating: 3
I have two tricks that make this the perfect chocolate cake. One--use one to two chocolate snack pudding cups for a truly moist cake. Put the pudding in at the same time you add the milk. Two... for the frosting... you don't really need the bowl of ice. Just use the mixer as directed. Then put it in the freezer for 15 minutes. Take it out. Use the mixer again. Keep doing it every 15 minutes until the frosting becomes stiff enough to spread. Every other instruction in this recipe is flawless.

Rating: 3
This cake does take time to make but worth the effort. Here are some tips from someone who's made it several times. 1-Add pudding to the cake mix. I use Snack pudding cups. Use 1 1/2 cups. This makes the cake a no-brainer for being extremely moist. 2-The frosting. I use ghiradelli milk chocolate chips. Once you transfer the chocolate to the bowl you can skip the whole ice bowl underneath and don't bother using the whisk. Instead. Use your average pair of beaters... mix it on medium for about 4 minutes or so. Then put the bowl in your freezer for 15 minutes. Take it out again and beat it some more for maybe two minutes and then put it back in the freezer. Do this three times. Total time it takes to make the frosting the right thickness is about 45 minutes or so. 3-I use a large Hershey Bar for the chocolate curls with a peeler. Everyone loves this cake and requests me to make it often.

