My oven underheats slightly, and 35 minutes seems fine for the cake. I wouldn't have a problem baking for 30 minutes, though. I always freeze my cakes for a day or so make transporting easier. The cake seems much moister after it has been frozen overnight. This cake has gotten rave reviews from my friends; I have made it 4 times, and will make it again. Leave off the fancy chocolate curls, or simply grate a little milk chocolate and/or sprinkle a few chopped Heath bars on top, it still looks good and is not as cloying. The frosting is delicious and the texture is good, even when it has been whipped too long. I have frozen the cake layers frosted and unfrosted, and both came out fine. Use good quality milk chocolate chips, or bags of unwrapped mini-kisses - don't bother to do any chopping. I have varied the sophistication of the milk chocolate flavor by mixing milk chocolates. And if the cake is a little cold when serving, a 7 to 10-second microwave blast brings out all the flavor and seems to moisten the cake more.

