Rating: 3
This cake looks spectacular-great for entertaining. I also had problems with the frosting. It would not whip up to soft peaks, more like a thick pudding consistency. I spread the frosting as well as possible using wax paper around the bottom of the cake dish to cake all the drips-and there was a lot of dripping! I saved about 1 cup of the frosting and refridgerated it overnight. The next day, it was thick and I went over the sides of the cake again with the thick frosting, added the chocolate shavings, removed the wax paper with the drippings and voila! It looked perfect and tasted great. My cake was also a bit dry, but my guests didn't think so at all!

